<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/stylesheets/listing4-2.css" />
    <title>Float based layouts</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="container">
      <header>
        <h1>Franklin Running Club</h1>
      </header>

      <main class="main clearfix">
        <h2>Running tips</h2>

        <div>
          <div class="media">
            <img
              src="/images/runner.png"
              alt="Person running."
              class="media-image"
            />
            <div class="media-body">
              <h4>Strength</h4>
              <p>
                Strength training is sn important part of injury pevention.
                Focus on your core&mdash; especially your abs and glutes.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="media">
            <img
              src="/images/shoes.png"
              alt="Image of a shoes"
              class="media-image"
            />
            <div class="media-body">
              <h4>Cadence</h4>
              <p>
                Check your stride turnover. The most efficient runner take about
                180 steps per minute.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="media">
            <img src="/images/shoes.png" alt="shoes" />
            <div class="media-body">
              <h4>Change it up</h4>
              <p>
                Don't run the same every time you hit the road. Vary your pace
                and the distance of yours runs.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="media">
            <img
              src="/images/runner.png"
              alt="Person running"
              class="media-image"
            />
            <div class="media-body">
              <h4>Focus on form</h4>
              <p>
                Run tall but relaxed. Your feet should hit the ground beneath
                your hips, not out in front you.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </main>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
